The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Cognizant sets foot in $1-bn club

 OUR BUREAU

 Mumbai, March 17: Cognizant has joined the billion-dollar club.

 The New Jersey-based technology solutions firm has recorded annualised revenues of over $1 billion in 2005, extrapolating fourth quarter revenues of $256 million.

 Actual revenues in 2005 were placed at $885.8 million in 2005, up 51 per cent over the previous year. The company has indicated a revenue guidance of at least $1.26 billion for calendar 2006.

 As a token of appreciation, the firm has handed out iPod Videos to its 18,000 Cognizant associates for reaching a major milestone in just 12 years.

 The fifth generation 30 GB memory iPod has been customised for Cognizant with a company logo engraved to celebrate the moment. It packs 75 hours of video, 7500 songs, and 12,500 photos.

 Cognizant has over 2,700 employees in Calcutta spread across four development centres. It operates out of its fully-owned development centre in Salt Lake and has three other leased facilities.

 Cognizant employs over 25,000 employees globally. 




